# TypeScript & Next.js

- Use strict TypeScript; prefer interfaces and shared types; avoid `any`.
- Use path aliases from `tsconfig.json` for imports.
- Next.js: prefer App Router (`app/`); functional components; colocate or use project CSS (e.g. `globals.css`, modules, or Tailwind as configured).
- Naming: camelCase (variables, functions), PascalCase (components, types), kebab-case for multi-word file/folder names when appropriate.
- Error handling: log and rethrow or return typed errors; avoid empty catch blocks.
